https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/getting-started.html
https://github.com/nodejs/node-gyp/issues/1045
1.	Install JDK 
2.	Install python 2.7
3.	Install android studio
4.	Install nodejs
5.	Install react-native-cli globally
 
6.	Creat app
 
7.	Open app folder with android studio and install missing platform 
8.	Add environment variable & edit path variable
 
 
9.	List and run emulator from cmd
 
cd /d  %ANDROID_HOME%/tools
C:\Users\AamirShahzad\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk\tools>emulator -avd Nexus_5X_API_26
10.	Open run and run  command
react-native start --reset-cache
or 
react-native start

11.	Run app
             react-native run-android
 
12.	To run on device run > open android folder in android studio > run app in device > repeat previous steps
